<concept id="a53b3d4de9251e4cdcd47b06b918b1e4" xml:lang="en-US">
   <title>Security Log Files</title>
   <prolog>
      <source>ST4 ID: 7603013515</source>
      <permissions view="ericsson_internal"/>
      <metadata>
         <othermeta content="NA" name="workitem"/>
      </metadata>
      <change-historylist/>
      <resourceid id="NA"/>
   </prolog>
   <conbody>
      <p>This section describes the security logs generated by <ph keyref="ECM"/> and OpenAM.</p>
      <section id="section_N10039_N1002E_N10001">
                           <title outputclass="st4mig_titled-block-title">Location of Security Log Files</title>
                           <p>The security log files are in the
               <filepath>/app/ecm/security/openAm/data/openam/log/</filepath> directory.</p>
                        </section>
      <section id="section_N1005B_N1002E_N10001">
                           <title outputclass="st4mig_titled-block-title">
                              <ph keyref="ECM"/> Logs API Operation Events</title>
                        </section>
      <section id="section_N1006A_N1002E_N10001"><!-- section wrapper added --><title outputclass="st4mig_titled-block-title"/>
                           <p>The <filepath>security.log</filepath> file logs these API events:</p>
                           <ul>
            <li>
                                 <p>The receiving of a REST layer API request.</p>
                              </li>
            <li>
                                 <p>Authorization of the REST layer API request.</p>
                              </li>
            <li>
                                 <p>Authentication of the REST layer request.</p>
                              </li>
            <li>
                                 <p>Completion, that is, returning of the REST layer request.</p>
                              </li>
         </ul>
                           <p>
                              <ph importance="normal">OpenAM, the OpenAM Logs Activities</ph>
                           </p>
                           <p>Separate access logs are created for each day. The file name includes the date in the format: </p><p>

                              <filepath>access_log.<parmname importance="normal">YYYY</parmname>-MM-DD</filepath>
                           </p>
                           <p>The access files log these activity events:</p>
                           <ul>
            <li>
                                 <p>Session activity, for example, logon, logout, session time-out, logon failure.</p>
                              </li>
            <li>
                                 <p>The creation, deletion and modification of identify-related entities, policies, and services.</p>
                              </li>
            <li>
                                 <p>The modification of user attributes, including passwords and group membership.</p>
                              </li>
            <li>
                                 <p>Delegation and data store activity.</p>
                              </li>
            <li>
                                 <p>Policy-related events, such as policy creation, deletion and modification, and policy evaluation.</p>
                              </li>
            <li>
                                 <p>Agent events and log resources allowed or denied to a user.</p>
                              </li>
            <li>
                                 <p>Events triggered by <option outputclass="st4mig_function">ssoadm</option> commands, or their administration console equivalent.</p>
                              </li>
         </ul>
                           <p>Descriptions of the log event fields: </p>
                           <note id="note_N10101_N1006A_N1002E_N10001">
                              <p>The fields contain different values depending on whether the log event was generated by <ph keyref="ECM"/> or by OpenAM.</p>
                           </note>
                           <ul>
            <li>
                                 <p><uicontrol>host</uicontrol> - The host IP address or the
                  hostname that the REST layer is running on – for example,
                  <option>shelob</option>.</p>
                              </li>
            <li>
                                 <p><uicontrol>pname</uicontrol> - <option>OPENAM</option> or the
                  REST layer operation name – for example, <option>createVm</option>,
                     <option>getOrder</option>.</p>
                              </li>
            <li>
                                 <p><uicontrol>appname</uicontrol> - <option>OPENAM</option> or
                     <option>ECM</option>.</p>
                              </li>
            <li>
                                 <p><uicontrol>subsys</uicontrol> - OpenAM subsystem or
                     <option>ECM_Services</option> concatenated with the module name processing the
                  event, for example, <option>ECM_Services.AuthenticationInterceptor</option>,
                     <option>ECM_Services.UserService</option>.</p>
                              </li>
            <li>
                                 <p><uicontrol>domain</uicontrol> - The Tenant associated with the
                  user.</p>
                              </li>
            <li>
                                 <p><uicontrol>user</uicontrol> – The user associated with the
                  event.</p>
                              </li>
            <li>
                                 <p><uicontrol>sev</uicontrol> – The event severity code (based on
                  RFC 5424).</p>
                              </li>
            <li>
                                 <p><uicontrol>time</uicontrol> – The time the log event is sent to
                  the <ph keyref="ECM"/> Log Collector.</p>
                              </li>
            <li>
                                 <p><uicontrol>event-time</uicontrol> – The time the log event
                  occurred.</p>
                              </li>
            <li>
                                 <p><uicontrol>rcvd-time</uicontrol> – The time <ph keyref="ECM"/>
                  Log Collector receives the log event.</p>
                              </li>
            <li>
                                 <p><uicontrol>rcvd-host</uicontrol> – The hostname receiving the
                  log events.</p>
                              </li>
            <li>
                                 <p><uicontrol>rcvd-pname</uicontrol> – The process name.</p>
                              </li>
            <li>
                                 <p><uicontrol>msg</uicontrol> – A message describing the event.</p>
                              </li>
            <li>
                                 <p><uicontrol>status</uicontrol> – <option>Success</option> or
                     <option>Failed</option>
               </p>
                              </li>
            <li>
                                 <p><uicontrol>pri</uicontrol> – The priority of the log event, for
                  example <option>WARN</option>, <option>INFO</option>, <option>ERROR</option>
               </p>
                              </li>
         </ul>
                        </section>
   </conbody>
</concept>